<subSubSection lastPageId="85" lastPageNumber="86" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1436,1759,2036]" box="[199,1424,1831,1856]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,1831,1856]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Description.</emphasis>
Based on 
<typeStatus box="[462,510,1832,1856]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">type</typeStatus>
description. Hototype complete, 
<quantity box="[883,962,1831,1856]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1033,1133,1831,1856]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.199999999999999" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" unit="mm" value="0.72">0.72 mm</quantity>
wide, about 55 segments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1436,1759,2036]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Venter anteriorly with mid-ventral groove and discrete ventro-lateral pads; pads incised with slight transverse grooves, extending from segment 4. Mid-ventral groove from segment 4.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1436,1759,2036]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
Buccal tentacles of 
<specimenCount box="[419,519,1939,1963]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" type="generic" typeStatus="type">one type</specimenCount>
. Upper lip prominent medial lobe, small wing-like lateral lobes, margin of medial lobe straight; oral surface glandular and ciliated. Outer lower lip flat, shield-like, pentagonal, large and cushionlike, ridged and grooved, extending posteriorly to segment 3 (
<figureCitation box="[843,940,2011,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 46" captionStartId="84.[151,250,1418,1440]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,204,1388]" captionTargetId="figure-199@84.[151,1436,193,1396]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURE 46. Polycirrus paivai Garraffoni &amp; Costa. a.Ventral view of head end. b. Capillary notochaeta from anteriorbody. c. Other kind of notochaeta from anterior body. e. Lateral view of anterior uncinus. e. Anterior view of notopodium from anteriormid body. Scales b, e=9.9 µm, c=20 µm, a=90 µm, e=22.2 µm. (Modified after Garraffoni &amp; Costa, 2003 and reproduced with permission from Zootaxa)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4948488/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Fig. 46a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3327330411" collectionCode="MF" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" specimenCount="1">
Notochaetigerous segments 12, extending to segment 14. Notopodia more-or-less rectangular, prechaetal lobe low, postchaetal lobe digitiform, longer than prechaetal (
<figureCitation box="[802,904,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 46" captionStartId="84.[151,250,1418,1440]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,204,1388]" captionTargetId="figure-199@84.[151,1436,193,1396]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURE 46. Polycirrus paivai Garraffoni &amp; Costa. a.Ventral view of head end. b. Capillary notochaeta from anteriorbody. c. Other kind of notochaeta from anterior body. e. Lateral view of anterior uncinus. e. Anterior view of notopodium from anteriormid body. Scales b, e=9.9 µm, c=20 µm, a=90 µm, e=22.2 µm. (Modified after Garraffoni &amp; Costa, 2003 and reproduced with permission from Zootaxa)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4948488/files/figure.png" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Fig. 46b</figureCitation>
). Notochaetae within a chaetiger consisting of 
<specimenCount box="[151,262,224,248]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
, pinnate (
<typeStatus box="[369,419,223,248]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">type</typeStatus>
description does not say if these are primary or secondary), posteriorly same form as those anteriorly; presumed secondary notochaetae in all chaetigers smooth, narrowly winged, uniformly tapered (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 46" captionStartId="84.[151,250,1418,1440]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,204,1388]" captionTargetId="figure-199@84.[151,1436,193,1396]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURE 46. Polycirrus paivai Garraffoni &amp; Costa. a.Ventral view of head end. b. Capillary notochaeta from anteriorbody. c. Other kind of notochaeta from anterior body. e. Lateral view of anterior uncinus. e. Anterior view of notopodium from anteriormid body. Scales b, e=9.9 µm, c=20 µm, a=90 µm, e=22.2 µm. (Modified after Garraffoni &amp; Costa, 2003 and reproduced with permission from Zootaxa)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4948488/files/figure.png" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Fig. 46c, d</figureCitation>
). Neurochaetae beginning on segment 12, 9–12 uncini per row throughout. Uncini with short neck and straight to convex base (
<typeStatus box="[430,488,332,357]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Type</typeStatus>
1), teeth above main fang arranged in double transverse series (
<collectionCode box="[1223,1272,332,357]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">MF</collectionCode>
:3:2) subrostral process present as low protuberance (
<figureCitation box="[570,667,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 46" captionStartId="84.[151,250,1418,1440]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,204,1388]" captionTargetId="figure-199@84.[151,1436,193,1396]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURE 46. Polycirrus paivai Garraffoni &amp; Costa. a.Ventral view of head end. b. Capillary notochaeta from anteriorbody. c. Other kind of notochaeta from anterior body. e. Lateral view of anterior uncinus. e. Anterior view of notopodium from anteriormid body. Scales b, e=9.9 µm, c=20 µm, a=90 µm, e=22.2 µm. (Modified after Garraffoni &amp; Costa, 2003 and reproduced with permission from Zootaxa)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4948488/files/figure.png" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Fig. 46e</figureCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1436,151,429]" box="[199,546,404,429]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Nephridial papillae not visible.</paragraph>
